<p>Some say a disclaimer, some say biscuiting, some say youthful na&iuml;vet&eacute; is the proper introduction for someone&rsquo;s piece of new literature.</p>

<p>When I was 16, my <a href="http://douglasgoetsch.com/">poetry teacher</a> had told us that the only unwritten preface we were allowed to give anything we had written was &ldquo;it&rsquo;s slightly new, but it smacks of genius&rdquo;.</p>